node.text: Civita di Bagnoregio in all its glory. ‘Twas a long journey to get here(taxi, train, bus, tears) but pasta lied ahead.. & nothing/nobody can get between me & my supper.
If I had a thousand lifetimes, I’d live them all in Italy.
I underestimated how lost one could actually get in these gardens & how much stamina it takes to get through them on a bike, but never doubt a lost American and her will to find an Aperol Spritz.
Post Truffle Hunting (& eating) we were shown the cutest of green houses.
Ever wonder how long those vines have been there? //Walking anywhere takes about 30 minutes longer than it should- due to my excessive photo taking.
Feels so wrong taking photos of someone’s delicates- but why must everything look so perfect in Italy? Even hung clothes have charm. 🍋

Went in for an espresso & left with what had just come out of their oven. Reasons why I love Italy. Everyone takes such pride in what they’ve made and just want to share it. The view was as good as that crusted fish!
That exposed brick peeking through paired with those perfect cracks. Greenery just where it needs to be. Perfection in all forms.
Workouts made easy with views like this.. 🏃🏼‍♀️ #romatherapy
If you’re even slightly considering a trip to Bagnoregio, I highly encourage it. Indeed is it a trek, but SO worth it. So much beauty to be taken in.

Back in November- fall foliage in true form// I’ll go ahead and assume the Italian who lives here doesn’t stand out front of it and take pics for the gram, but I do hope they appreciate it as much as I do.
I’ll never know how that red car got out, but I did wait a bit just to guiltily catch a reaction.. Really hoping a cannoli was left on his windshield.
Reflections are my favorite, especially with gelato in hand. 🍨 📷 ☁️

I grew up playing basketball, so coming across this at a friends home caused some serious excitement. Cobblestone & a hoop, my two favorite things! #rome #italy #basketball #cobblestone #roma #travel #zagaroloroma #zagarolo #italia
Cobblestone meets potted plants. Ever seen a better combination? Exploring this little City has been nothing shy of amazing. If you haven’t discovered Bagnoregio yet, add it to your list!
Italy, you are perfection.
Alright y’all, let’s all take a minute to thank the gelato gods. 🙌🏻 This view pairing is everything. Pistachio, you never disappoint.
Walked past this with my head in my phone. The greenery caught my eye.. sadly almost missed such a sight. Slow it down & stop to enjoy the view today, there’s beauty waiting on every corner.

Took a drive just outside of Naples to discover this beauty. The plan was to hike Mount Vesuvius... Though little did we know it had been completely burned down on one side and closed off to the public. Instead we explored a hotel & took advantage of their view!
Have you ever seen something more beautiful? If you’ve never seen Eat, Pray, Love- I suggest you get on it! & if you’ve never had an Eat, Pray, Love moment of your own- I encourage you.
When getting lost in the gardens turns out beautifully. This view was too perfect not to have lunch in front of. #rome_rooftops #roma #italy #views
-Everything tastes better in Italy- A phrase I so commonly use. I’d say it could just be in my head, but there are enough people out there to back me up, for me to believe it is in fact 100% true.
Took a day trip to Frascati for a wine & rain pairing...Unbeknownst to me, one of the greatest pairings I’ve been missing out on all these years. Just a quick train ride away from Rome!

Population of 7 during winter to 100 in summer. No cars or reception. Just  pasta, beauty & charm. I too, thought towns like this only existed in storybooks. #tlpicks #italy #bagnoregio #civitadibagnoregio #italia
Being on that no calorie left behind experiment, calls for daily runs... side note- I asked for a fall foliage & got it! 🍂 though it came with a pair of love handles. (That.. well, I didn’t ask for)
